race.description: Phil Green’s 'A Big Turkey’ Classic Maiden Plate
race.comment: Tricky race. FIRE TYPE (4) has upside and that could prove the difference. Two runs this time in have been good, sticking on well for third there in a decent maiden. He should relish getting to 1600m now being by The Autumn Sun and can get the job done. TITAN'S SPIRIT (2) wasn't beaten all that far at Geelong last time out over 1512m four weeks ago. Fitter and the blinkers are back on. Appeals as a leading player. HALLOWED HALLS (5) ran a better race finishing midfield last start at Geelong when well in the market. Could be an improver at his third start with the addition of blinkers. NARAGHI (11) returns from a lay-off. Placed in a recent trial at Caulfield Heath and has claims.
